# === ntfy phone-push alerts — the ONLY signal channel (Discord retired 2026-07-23) ===
# The bot defaults to the "aharg-ops" topic in code, so this is optional; set it
# only to point somewhere else. Whoever knows the topic can read the alerts —
# keep it private. Subscribe on your phone (ntfy app → add topic "aharg-ops",
# or open https://ntfy.sh/aharg-ops). Test delivery: python ntfy_notifier.py --test
NTFY_TOPIC=aharg-ops
# Optional: self-hosted server (default https://ntfy.sh)
# NTFY_SERVER=https://ntfy.sh
# Optional: access token for a protected/self-hosted topic (Bearer auth)
# NTFY_TOKEN=tk_YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

# === Discord — RETIRED. Left here only for the data scraper + legacy --discord opt-in. ===
# Signal alerts no longer post to Discord. discord_bot.py stays in the tree; the
# scanner posts to Discord only if you pass --discord explicitly.
# DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/YOUR_WEBHOOK_ID/YOUR_WEBHOOK_TOKEN

# Discord bot token for the data scraper (discord_scraper.py) — unrelated to alerts.
# DISCORD_DATA_TOKEN=YOUR_BOT_TOKEN_HERE
